sql:
SELECT AVG(average_percentage) AS avg_support
FROM polling_trends
WHERE candidate_id = 1 AND election_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(margin_of_error) AS average_margin_of_error
FROM polling_data
WHERE pollster_id = 1;

SELECT pollster_name
FROM pollsters
WHERE pollster_id = 1;

SELECT poll_id
FROM polling_data
WHERE biden_percentage > 50;

SELECT pollster_name
FROM pollsters
ORDER BY pollster_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- A reliable poll refers to one with a sample size greater than 500 and a margin of error less than 5; 
- Substantial support means an average combined support percentage for Biden and Trump greater than 50; 
- Large sample size and small margin of error are indicators of a reliable poll.

